Date:  16/7/1945
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  33
Edition:
Quote:  After a farmer has decided on the area to be bordered it should be ploughed and worked up. After bordering it should occasionally be worked up to keep down weeds, at the same time consolidating the land to produce the firm seed-bed so desirable for grass and clover seed.
